1
00:00:01,610 --> 00:00:05,640
[Episode 9: Prisoner of Time]

2
00:00:22,820 --> 00:00:25,250
Happy birthday to you.

3
00:00:26,820 --> 00:00:27,980
Happy birthday.

4
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,080
When you become famous in the future,

5
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:51,750
I'll show off to everyone

6
00:00:51,750 --> 00:00:53,150
that I was your first fan.

7
00:00:55,550 --> 00:00:56,580
Then

8
00:00:57,130 --> 00:00:58,790
no one will see how sad you are.

9
00:01:00,610 --> 00:01:02,740
I've accepted reality a long time ago.

10
00:01:02,860 --> 00:01:04,390
The whole world hates me.

11
00:01:04,629 --> 00:01:06,060
No one likes me.

12
00:01:18,570 --> 00:01:19,400
Are you crazy?

13
00:01:26,350 --> 00:01:27,550
He Xiangyong!

14
00:01:29,620 --> 00:01:30,490
He Xiangyong!

15
00:01:30,520 --> 00:01:31,920
Chen Haowei, please don't go.

16
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:32,850
-Please don't leave!
-Don't stop me!

17
00:01:32,850 --> 00:01:33,960
Chen Haowei.

18
00:02:43,760 --> 00:02:46,840
[Wishing Upon the Shooting Stars]

19
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:49,430
Chen Haowei.

20
00:02:49,860 --> 00:02:51,100
Chen Haowei.

21
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:51,570
Chen Haowei.

22
00:02:51,570 --> 00:02:52,200
Wake up.

23
00:02:52,470 --> 00:02:53,000
Wake up!

24
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:53,570
Why are we here?

25
00:02:53,570 --> 00:02:55,230
How did we get back yesterday?

26
00:02:55,530 --> 00:02:56,230
Get up.

27
00:02:56,260 --> 00:02:57,530
Get up!

28
00:02:57,810 --> 00:02:59,030
How did we get back yesterday?

29
00:02:59,030 --> 00:03:00,880
We were on the main island yesterday.

30
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:01,880
Didn't we go eat,

31
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:03,750
then take a walk,

32
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,010
and later, there were no boats,
so we stayed at a hotel?

33
00:03:05,010 --> 00:03:06,010
Don't you remember?

34
00:03:06,010 --> 00:03:07,380
We've been staying at the guesthouse.

35
00:03:07,380 --> 00:03:08,080
What are you talking about?

36
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:08,680
Wake up.

37
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:09,950
Look at me.

38
00:03:09,970 --> 00:03:11,180
Wake up. Look at me.

39
00:03:11,470 --> 00:03:12,690
Are you messing with me?

40
00:03:12,690 --> 00:03:14,020
Are you messing with me?

41
00:03:14,090 --> 00:03:14,990
Hold on.

42
00:03:14,990 --> 00:03:16,720
You're the one messing with me.

43
00:03:17,060 --> 00:03:18,329
What are you talking about, Zhong Xiaoyou?

44
00:03:18,329 --> 00:03:19,890
Let me sleep a little more.

45
00:03:19,890 --> 00:03:21,340
What did you call me?

46
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,220
Why did you call me Zhong Xiaoyou?

47
00:03:23,670 --> 00:03:24,820
What else should I call you?

48
00:03:24,820 --> 00:03:25,720
Have...

49
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:28,060
Have I changed?

50
00:03:30,860 --> 00:03:31,860
No.

51
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,050
I'm He Xiangyong.

52
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,950
What time is it now?

53
00:03:34,980 --> 00:03:36,610
How is that possible?

54
00:03:37,890 --> 00:03:39,590
I'm not Zhong Xiaoyou.

55
00:03:39,620 --> 00:03:40,820
I'm not Zhong Xiaoyou.

56
00:03:40,820 --> 00:03:42,190
I'm He Xiangyong.

57
00:03:44,260 --> 00:03:45,600
I'm He Xiangyong.

58
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:47,120
Calm down.

59
00:03:47,579 --> 00:03:48,410
Calm down.

60
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:49,650
Calm down, okay?

61
00:03:50,579 --> 00:03:51,980
Did you have a nightmare?

62
00:03:53,110 --> 00:03:54,720
Get some rest.

63
00:03:57,660 --> 00:03:59,760
Wow, you just bought this?

64
00:03:59,780 --> 00:04:01,240
What? Trying to redeem yourself?

65
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,240
What do you mean?

66
00:04:02,260 --> 00:04:03,490
You're the king of getting skunked.

67
00:04:03,490 --> 00:04:04,830
Do I need redemption?

68
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:06,280
Let me take a look.

69
00:04:06,770 --> 00:04:08,410
-What?
-How did I get back yesterday?

70
00:04:08,410 --> 00:04:09,340
How did I get back yesterday?

71
00:04:09,340 --> 00:04:10,300
What are you talking about?

72
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:11,160
Yeah.

73
00:04:24,650 --> 00:04:26,250
Xiaoyou, what are you doing?

74
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:29,960
Why are there only photos
of you and Uncle Hua?

75
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:31,420
Where's the family photo?

76
00:04:31,420 --> 00:04:32,820
What family photo?

77
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:33,790
Mom...

78
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:35,740
Where are the photos
of your wife and your son?

79
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:37,600
And why are all the trophies gone?

80
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,330
You've been married before?

81
00:04:40,330 --> 00:04:42,880
If I ever got married, you'd be
the most handsome guy on Xingpu Island.

82
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:43,570
We've known each other this long,

83
00:04:43,570 --> 00:04:44,900
and you don't know if I'm married?

84
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:46,430
What are you talking about?

85
00:04:47,450 --> 00:04:48,980
You've never been married?

86
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:56,140
Xiaoyou, you've been working here
for three to four months.

87
00:04:56,140 --> 00:04:58,340
Why don't you know if he's been married?

88
00:05:00,060 --> 00:05:01,430
Be gentle. What are you doing?

89
00:05:01,430 --> 00:05:02,430
There are many things in the cabinet.

90
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:03,500
Be careful.

91
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:06,770
I think his condition is very serious.

92
00:05:06,770 --> 00:05:07,800
Take a look at him.

93
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:08,770
I'm a surgeon.

94
00:05:08,770 --> 00:05:10,310
Maybe he just hit his head

95
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:11,540
and something's wrong with it.

96
00:05:11,540 --> 00:05:12,540
Take a look at him.

97
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:15,570
That's impossible.

98
00:05:15,910 --> 00:05:16,710
Xiaoyou,

99
00:05:16,730 --> 00:05:18,050
the clinic is over there.

100
00:05:18,050 --> 00:05:19,750
Yes, let him take a look at you.

101
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:22,300
Gosh.

102
00:05:41,870 --> 00:05:43,200
Gosh.

103
00:05:44,550 --> 00:05:45,650
Gosh.

104
00:05:46,540 --> 00:05:48,450
Gosh!

105
00:05:48,470 --> 00:05:50,300
Mom!

106
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:55,040
Do you want me to wash
your bed sheets or your pants?

107
00:05:57,700 --> 00:05:58,290
Why did you call me?

108
00:05:58,290 --> 00:06:00,190
Mom, why am I home?

109
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,560
Where would you be if you weren't home?

110
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,790
No, listen. I went

111
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:05,490
to bail Soukai out yesterday,
and it got really late after that.

112
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:06,250
There...

113
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:06,980
There were no boats back.

114
00:06:06,980 --> 00:06:08,470
So we just found a random hotel.

115
00:06:08,470 --> 00:06:09,730
-We slept after we checked in.
-Mr. Li.

116
00:06:09,730 --> 00:06:10,320
After we sleep...

117
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:11,620
Mr. Li.

118
00:06:12,170 --> 00:06:13,700
What are you talking about?

119
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:14,970
It was your birthday yesterday.

120
00:06:14,970 --> 00:06:16,700
We had tomahawk steak at home,

121
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:17,180
right?

122
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,060
It was so big.

123
00:06:18,090 --> 00:06:19,230
You said it was delicious.

124
00:06:19,230 --> 00:06:20,360
Have you forgotten?

125
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:21,430
Tomahawk steak?

126
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,150
This isn't a dream.

127
00:06:23,730 --> 00:06:25,990
I have no idea what you're talking about.

128
00:06:26,570 --> 00:06:27,170
Mom,

129
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:28,520
I'm taking leave today.

130
00:06:31,620 --> 00:06:32,720
Hama-chan.

131
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:34,590
Hama-chan.

132
00:06:38,150 --> 00:06:39,250
Hama-chan.

133
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:41,409
Hama-chan.

134
00:06:41,409 --> 00:06:42,010
What?

135
00:06:42,010 --> 00:06:44,210
Yesterday, let me tell you, yesterday—

136
00:06:44,620 --> 00:06:45,850
Where's your wound?

137
00:06:45,850 --> 00:06:47,090
What wound?

138
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:49,520
We were
on the main island yesterday, right?

139
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:51,320
Then I went to the police station

140
00:06:51,610 --> 00:06:52,409
because you seemed to have a fight—

141
00:06:52,409 --> 00:06:53,370
I'm busy today.

142
00:06:53,390 --> 00:06:55,530
Let's talk when you're back.

143
00:06:57,730 --> 00:06:58,990
Just hear me out first.

144
00:06:59,070 --> 00:07:00,070
Hama-chan.

145
00:07:11,510 --> 00:07:13,540
Li Wanzhe.

146
00:07:15,410 --> 00:07:16,480
Where have you been?

147
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:17,850
I've been looking for you.

148
00:07:17,850 --> 00:07:18,550
What are you doing?

149
00:07:18,550 --> 00:07:19,520
Something happened.

150
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:20,590
What happened?

151
00:07:20,590 --> 00:07:22,250
I was on the main island last night.

152
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:24,390
But when I woke up today,
I came back to Xingpu Island.

153
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:25,490
Me too.

154
00:07:25,490 --> 00:07:27,090
I somehow woke up back on Xingpu Island.

155
00:07:27,090 --> 00:07:28,090
You too?

156
00:07:29,590 --> 00:07:30,530
What should we do?

157
00:07:30,530 --> 00:07:32,430
Is this because of
the wish made upon the shooting stars?

158
00:07:32,430 --> 00:07:34,360
Wish made upon the shooting stars?

159
00:07:34,530 --> 00:07:36,000
How do you know I made a wish?

160
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:36,659
Idiot.

161
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,300
We made it together.

162
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:39,440
I didn't.

163
00:07:40,470 --> 00:07:42,810
That night, weren't we
at that banquet dinner?

164
00:07:42,810 --> 00:07:44,110
Then your mom shoved a mic at me.

165
00:07:44,110 --> 00:07:45,340
I told everyone I was fired.

166
00:07:45,340 --> 00:07:46,610
I went to the beach platform,
you came to me,

167
00:07:46,610 --> 00:07:47,610
and we made wishes together.

168
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:48,510
Do you forget?

169
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:49,880
What were you talking about?

170
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:52,140
I've never had a banquet dinner with you.

171
00:07:54,530 --> 00:07:55,630
Li Wanzhe.

172
00:07:56,690 --> 00:07:58,190
What's my name?

173
00:07:58,490 --> 00:07:59,520
Zhong Xiaoyou.

174
00:07:59,540 --> 00:08:00,810
What Zhong Xiaoyou?

175
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:02,040
I'm He Xiangyong!

176
00:08:02,170 --> 00:08:03,140
He Xiangyong?

177
00:08:03,690 --> 00:08:04,500
Who is it?

178
00:08:06,030 --> 00:08:07,090
Let me tell you.

179
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:08,590
No matter how you know it,

180
00:08:08,590 --> 00:08:10,290
I hope you don't tell anyone.

181
00:08:11,270 --> 00:08:12,240
Li Wanzhe.

182
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,200
Li Wanzhe, you...

183
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,170
Li Wanzhe!

184
00:08:17,710 --> 00:08:19,910
This is bad.

185
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:21,650
What's the problem?

186
00:08:21,670 --> 00:08:22,840
Why did this happen?

187
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:36,289
You're back.

188
00:08:37,539 --> 00:08:38,490
Are you okay?

189
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,170
A girl called Xixi

190
00:08:45,170 --> 00:08:46,170
called you just now.

191
00:08:46,170 --> 00:08:47,700
She said she's your friend.

192
00:08:49,870 --> 00:08:50,810
What did she say?

193
00:08:53,410 --> 00:08:55,280
At first, she was looking
for He Xiangyong,

194
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:56,810
then she asked for you.

195
00:08:57,650 --> 00:08:59,110
She left her phone number.

196
00:09:03,870 --> 00:09:05,470
So who is He Xiangyong?

197
00:09:34,990 --> 00:09:35,940
Hello, Xixi.

198
00:09:36,290 --> 00:09:37,560
Do you remember me?

199
00:09:39,260 --> 00:09:41,680
Although you're not the managing editor
in my memory,

200
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:43,010
I just thought of you,

201
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:44,220
He Xiangyong.

202
00:09:48,310 --> 00:09:49,880
Thank God.

203
00:09:51,070 --> 00:09:52,530
Xixi, listen to me.

204
00:09:53,340 --> 00:09:54,110
Last night

205
00:09:54,110 --> 00:09:55,740
I was clearly staying with Chen Haowei
at a hotel on the main island.

206
00:09:55,740 --> 00:09:56,670
But when I opened my eyes today,

207
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:58,080
I was on Xingpu Island.

208
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,140
I asked Chen Haowei.

209
00:09:59,140 --> 00:09:59,740
But he told me

210
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:01,010
he doesn't know who He Xiangyong is.

211
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:03,010
But he recognized me last night.

212
00:10:03,010 --> 00:10:03,950
Then I asked my dad.

213
00:10:03,950 --> 00:10:05,880
But my dad told me he was never married.

214
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:06,680
All the decorations in my house—

215
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:07,290
my photos,

216
00:10:07,290 --> 00:10:08,220
my mom's photos,

217
00:10:08,220 --> 00:10:08,790
even my family portrait

218
00:10:08,790 --> 00:10:09,850
were gone.

219
00:10:09,850 --> 00:10:10,990
Then I went to Li Wanzhe.

220
00:10:10,990 --> 00:10:12,520
Li Wanzhe also told me
that he couldn't recognize me.

221
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:13,360
But before that,

222
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:14,660
he was the only one

223
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:15,760
-who remembered me—
-Calm down.

224
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:16,930
Listen to me.

225
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,260
I dreamed that I went to Xingpu Island

226
00:10:20,260 --> 00:10:22,100
and met someone outside the grocery store

227
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:24,230
who knew I like bitter gourd black tea.

228
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:26,530
The grocery store.

229
00:10:27,570 --> 00:10:29,410
Is that Hong?

230
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:31,710
He said every wish

231
00:10:31,730 --> 00:10:33,480
comes with losing something.

232
00:10:34,810 --> 00:10:37,880
I think the wish is starting to backfire.

233
00:10:38,420 --> 00:10:41,020
Time and space
are starting to get disordered.

234
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:46,220
The card I drew

235
00:10:46,220 --> 00:10:48,160
also proved what Hong said.

236
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:52,390
So if I got Zhong Xiaoyou's identity,

237
00:10:52,390 --> 00:10:54,530
does that mean He Xiangyong
had to disappear?

238
00:10:54,530 --> 00:10:56,280
Was everything I wished for

239
00:10:56,310 --> 00:10:57,810
really this temporary?

240
00:10:58,270 --> 00:10:59,270
Xixi, what should I do?

241
00:10:59,270 --> 00:11:01,010
I finally made up with my dad.

242
00:11:01,010 --> 00:11:01,610
And I finally

243
00:11:01,610 --> 00:11:02,910
got another chance with Chen Haowei.

244
00:11:02,910 --> 00:11:04,780
What can I do to make it right?

245
00:11:04,780 --> 00:11:06,040
What can I do

246
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:07,040
to bring everything back to normal?

247
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,110
Xixi, can you help me?

248
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:09,150
He Xiangyong.

249
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:11,090
If you give up now,

250
00:11:11,110 --> 00:11:12,510
the game will be over.

251
00:11:15,970 --> 00:11:17,500
Go find Hong first.

252
00:11:18,620 --> 00:11:19,860
Why?

253
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,990
I don't think he's an ordinary person.

254
00:11:21,990 --> 00:11:23,490
Maybe only he can help you.

255
00:11:38,590 --> 00:11:40,090
Hong!

256
00:11:41,610 --> 00:11:43,180
Hong!

257
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:57,260
Mr. De.

258
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:58,710
Have you seen Hong?

259
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:00,560
He's not sitting outside?

260
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:01,130
No.

261
00:12:01,130 --> 00:12:01,910
No.

262
00:12:27,790 --> 00:12:30,460
[What happens
when you wish upon the shooting stars?]

263
00:12:32,370 --> 00:12:33,470
[Sorry. The system cannot
solve your problem.]

264
00:12:37,970 --> 00:12:40,000
Even AI can't solve it.

265
00:12:40,710 --> 00:12:42,240
What should I do?

266
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:47,550
Li Wanzhe, my sweet soup is ready.

267
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:48,610
Take it down for me.

268
00:12:48,980 --> 00:12:50,000
Li Wanzhe.

269
00:12:50,180 --> 00:12:51,500
What are you doing?

270
00:12:51,730 --> 00:12:53,000
Get down to work.

271
00:12:53,330 --> 00:12:54,620
You pull the same stunt every day.

272
00:12:54,620 --> 00:12:55,750
You're so annoying.

273
00:12:56,130 --> 00:12:57,000
Tao.

274
00:12:57,260 --> 00:12:58,200
You're here.

275
00:12:58,760 --> 00:12:59,920
You're here too, Village Chief?

276
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:00,450
Okay.

277
00:13:05,190 --> 00:13:06,810
I'll give you fewer tapioca pearls

278
00:13:06,810 --> 00:13:08,080
and more mung beans, okay?

279
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:08,500
Sure.

280
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:09,270
Okay.

281
00:13:09,270 --> 00:13:09,900
Wanzhe's mom.

282
00:13:09,900 --> 00:13:11,240
Have you seen Hong?

283
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:12,030
Hong?

284
00:13:12,050 --> 00:13:13,270
Why are you looking for him?

285
00:13:13,270 --> 00:13:14,110
Isn't he staying at the temple?

286
00:13:14,110 --> 00:13:15,470
I have something important to ask him.

287
00:13:15,470 --> 00:13:16,740
He lives behind the temple.

288
00:13:16,740 --> 00:13:18,810
No, he lives in the sixth house
from the end on Seaside Road.

289
00:13:18,810 --> 00:13:19,880
But I remember him staying
at the grocery store before.

290
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:20,480
What are you talking about?

291
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:22,310
He lives next to the dock.

292
00:13:22,310 --> 00:13:23,510
He lives behind the temple.

293
00:13:23,510 --> 00:13:25,620
He used to lay a straw mat there

294
00:13:25,620 --> 00:13:26,780
and do laundry.

295
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:28,590
Li Wanzhe.

296
00:13:28,620 --> 00:13:29,980
What do you want?

297
00:13:31,860 --> 00:13:33,560
I know you don't trust me now.

298
00:13:33,890 --> 00:13:35,350
But I still want to tell you

299
00:13:35,630 --> 00:13:37,630
that if we want to solve the problem,

300
00:13:37,660 --> 00:13:39,330
Hong seems to be the key.

301
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:41,130
Do we know each other well?

302
00:13:41,130 --> 00:13:43,060
And why do you know so much about me?

303
00:13:43,180 --> 00:13:44,780
I warn you not to tell anyone.

304
00:13:45,740 --> 00:13:47,440
I didn't.

305
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:50,340
Xiaoyou.

306
00:13:50,370 --> 00:13:52,100
Haowei, do you want shaved ice?

307
00:13:52,270 --> 00:13:53,440
Later.

308
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:54,280
Okay.

309
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:54,810
Xiaoyou.

310
00:13:54,810 --> 00:13:55,810
Hurry and come back with me.

311
00:13:55,810 --> 00:13:57,280
Mr. He is already angry.

312
00:13:57,950 --> 00:13:59,050
Here, take it.

313
00:13:59,870 --> 00:14:01,130
Are you skipping work?

314
00:14:01,650 --> 00:14:02,520
Go home.

315
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:06,380
What?

316
00:14:06,490 --> 00:14:08,550
Why did you disappear after the call?

317
00:14:10,130 --> 00:14:11,060
See you.

318
00:14:11,430 --> 00:14:12,060
Bye-bye.

319
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:13,120
Take care.

320
00:14:13,150 --> 00:14:13,780
Okay!

321
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,440
Weirdo.

322
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,940
What do you want to tell me?

323
00:14:46,660 --> 00:14:48,030
First time in two months

324
00:14:49,340 --> 00:14:50,940
I've seen you this panicked.

325
00:15:00,970 --> 00:15:02,030
Alright.

326
00:15:02,470 --> 00:15:04,730
It's okay if you don't want
to tell me now.

327
00:15:17,850 --> 00:15:18,660
Just tell me

328
00:15:18,660 --> 00:15:19,860
when you want to.

329
00:15:25,380 --> 00:15:28,180
I'll call Mr. He and tell him
we're going back late.

330
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:30,150
Where do you want to go?

331
00:15:37,650 --> 00:15:38,820
Come on.

332
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,480
Let's be cheesy.

333
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:41,450
Come on.

334
00:15:41,810 --> 00:15:42,940
Let's be cheesy.

335
00:16:03,020 --> 00:16:04,220
You're finally back.

336
00:16:05,640 --> 00:16:07,040
You've searched for Hong

337
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:10,080
so hard
that the whole Xingpu Island knows.

338
00:16:10,350 --> 00:16:12,290
Well, have you found it?

339
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:22,210
What's wrong with you?

340
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:24,860
No matter what happened,

341
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:26,890
you can't run away without a word.

342
00:16:27,130 --> 00:16:29,190
Then who's handling the guesthouse?

343
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:30,890
Haowei or me?

344
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:31,840
Mr. He.

345
00:16:32,170 --> 00:16:33,900
Xiaoyou must have a reason

346
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:37,700
-for looking for Hong like this...
-He has a mouth. Don't interrupt.

347
00:16:38,780 --> 00:16:40,640
You're acting strange today.

348
00:16:40,660 --> 00:16:42,390
You don't even want to explain.

349
00:16:44,550 --> 00:16:45,320
I'm sorry.

350
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:48,750
I'll solve my own problem.

351
00:16:49,090 --> 00:16:51,890
I won't let it affect
the guesthouse work anymore.

352
00:16:58,730 --> 00:16:59,760
Forget it.

353
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:02,870
You young people have your own ideas.

354
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:07,970
But if there's really something

355
00:17:07,970 --> 00:17:09,510
you can't solve,

356
00:17:10,609 --> 00:17:11,740
even if you don't want to tell me,

357
00:17:11,740 --> 00:17:12,940
you can go to Uncle Hua

358
00:17:12,940 --> 00:17:14,510
or Angela.

359
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:16,710
After all, we're elders.

360
00:17:16,710 --> 00:17:18,420
You can discuss with us.

361
00:17:25,420 --> 00:17:26,260
Xiaoyou.

362
00:17:26,890 --> 00:17:27,589
You've been busy all day.

363
00:17:27,589 --> 00:17:28,690
You must be hungry.

364
00:17:29,190 --> 00:17:30,150
I'll get you something to eat.

365
00:17:30,150 --> 00:17:30,980
Wait for me.

366
00:17:32,710 --> 00:17:34,180
Let's eat. I'm hungry.

367
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:46,720
Let's eat.

368
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:50,450
Thank you, Mr. He.

369
00:18:25,050 --> 00:18:27,120
Hey. Is it bad?

370
00:18:30,310 --> 00:18:33,920
My parents
love garlic shrimp vermicelli, too.

371
00:18:42,770 --> 00:18:44,570
Go home if you miss home.

372
00:18:44,970 --> 00:18:46,170
No need to take leave.

373
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:55,210
Let's go and rest.

374
00:18:55,210 --> 00:18:56,480
Here.

375
00:19:01,320 --> 00:19:02,390
Are you okay?

376
00:19:31,450 --> 00:19:32,350
Sisi.

377
00:19:32,750 --> 00:19:33,520
I'm here to get

378
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:35,250
the black sugar my mom ordered.

379
00:19:35,580 --> 00:19:36,410
Hold on.

380
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:37,560
My dad is taking a shower.

381
00:19:37,560 --> 00:19:38,660
Okay, thank you.

382
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:40,180
Old man.

383
00:19:40,610 --> 00:19:41,780
It's Wanzhe.

384
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:57,700
Hong.

385
00:19:58,580 --> 00:20:00,810
Do you know something
about wishing on shooting stars?

386
00:20:00,810 --> 00:20:02,410
Why did Zhong Xiaoyou
keep saying you are...

387
00:20:02,410 --> 00:20:03,750
you are the key.

388
00:20:03,750 --> 00:20:04,780
What do you mean?

389
00:20:04,780 --> 00:20:06,050
I didn't make a wish.

390
00:20:06,050 --> 00:20:06,750
Did you?

391
00:20:07,370 --> 00:20:08,340
I do.

392
00:20:08,670 --> 00:20:09,670
What did you make?

393
00:20:10,150 --> 00:20:11,490
I didn't make a wish.

394
00:20:11,510 --> 00:20:12,870
I never made a wish.

395
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:14,840
It's all a secret.

396
00:20:15,730 --> 00:20:16,830
Secret?

397
00:20:18,230 --> 00:20:19,560
What do you mean?

398
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:22,530
In this world,

399
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:25,400
no secret stays hidden forever.

400
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:28,610
One day, the sea will tell you

401
00:20:29,340 --> 00:20:30,990
what it wants to say.

402
00:20:33,380 --> 00:20:34,610
It's right here.

403
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:36,510
What sea?

404
00:20:36,980 --> 00:20:39,320
Love burns like fireworks,

405
00:20:39,320 --> 00:20:41,050
like everything's on fire.

406
00:20:41,830 --> 00:20:44,200
On fire? What fire?

407
00:20:44,290 --> 00:20:46,090
Hong, what are you trying to say?

408
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:48,490
I want to ask you why Zhong Xiaoyou—

409
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:52,420
Here.

410
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:55,160
This is for you.

411
00:20:56,070 --> 00:20:57,330
Don't come to me again.

412
00:20:57,830 --> 00:20:59,200
I'm going home.

413
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:00,970
I want to go back to my home in the sea.

414
00:21:00,970 --> 00:21:02,270
I can finally go home.

415
00:21:02,270 --> 00:21:03,310
Wanzhe.

416
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:09,240
My dad asked you to move it yourself.

417
00:21:09,910 --> 00:21:11,970
Don't sunglasses make it hard to see?

418
00:21:12,350 --> 00:21:14,810
That's the rocker vibe.
You wouldn't get it.

419
00:21:24,570 --> 00:21:25,470
It's raining.

420
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:26,940
Why don't you go down?

421
00:21:29,380 --> 00:21:31,240
I want to sit here a little longer.

422
00:21:51,460 --> 00:21:53,010
Go home if you want.

423
00:21:54,810 --> 00:21:56,610
Don't worry about the work here.

424
00:21:57,130 --> 00:21:58,300
I'll do it.

425
00:21:59,820 --> 00:22:01,400
This is my home.

426
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:06,010
You don't believe me?

427
00:22:11,850 --> 00:22:13,310
You really don't.

428
00:22:18,090 --> 00:22:19,490
Have you heard of déjà vu?

429
00:22:29,630 --> 00:22:31,330
Déjà vu is the strange feeling

430
00:22:32,170 --> 00:22:34,630
that you've experienced something before.

431
00:22:36,230 --> 00:22:37,570
Lately, every time I talk to you,

432
00:22:37,570 --> 00:22:38,940
I get déjà vu.

433
00:22:45,980 --> 00:22:48,240
Actually, I'm curious about something.

434
00:22:50,790 --> 00:22:53,720
You said I was
He Xiangyong's high school classmate.

435
00:22:55,420 --> 00:22:57,120
And you said you were He Xiangyong.

436
00:22:57,120 --> 00:22:58,060
Well,

437
00:22:59,060 --> 00:23:01,260
did anything happen between us before?

438
00:23:10,030 --> 00:23:11,560
When you were in 12th grade,

439
00:23:12,370 --> 00:23:13,870
you lost in basketball.

440
00:23:15,910 --> 00:23:17,980
I put my hat on your head,

441
00:23:19,340 --> 00:23:21,740
because I didn't want people
to see you sad.

442
00:23:26,650 --> 00:23:28,980
In my 12th grade, I didn't play basketball

443
00:23:29,990 --> 00:23:31,720
for the college entrance exam.

444
00:23:35,210 --> 00:23:37,010
On your 18th birthday,

445
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:39,310
I drew a sea turtle drawing for you

446
00:23:40,170 --> 00:23:41,880
as your birthday gift.

447
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:45,860
But I've never received
any sea turtle drawing.

448
00:23:46,340 --> 00:23:47,570
Do you remember

449
00:23:48,470 --> 00:23:50,370
you liked to tell cold jokes?

450
00:24:11,380 --> 00:24:13,380
The necklace on your neck

451
00:24:15,370 --> 00:24:16,800
is also from me.

452
00:24:19,590 --> 00:24:20,920
This necklace

453
00:24:22,670 --> 00:24:25,200
was a gift from me
when I was on the main island.

454
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:29,620
Forget it.

455
00:24:30,950 --> 00:24:32,650
It's pointless.

456
00:24:33,780 --> 00:24:35,440
You don't remember it anyway.

457
00:24:36,420 --> 00:24:39,150
The more I say it,
the more disappointed I will be.

458
00:24:44,190 --> 00:24:45,800
I think it's interesting.

459
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,500
And you can draw.

460
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:52,700
I've always admired people who can draw.

461
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:58,770
I want to follow your art

462
00:24:58,890 --> 00:25:00,320
forever and always,

463
00:25:00,850 --> 00:25:02,650
and be your biggest fan forever.

464
00:25:05,430 --> 00:25:07,560
Actually, I kind of remember

465
00:25:08,620 --> 00:25:10,050
what you just told me.

466
00:25:13,460 --> 00:25:15,390
Didn't you say you don't remember?

467
00:25:17,550 --> 00:25:18,950
It's déjà vu.

468
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:23,430
The man in my dream is vague.

469
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:25,900
I can't see his face clearly.

470
00:25:27,740 --> 00:25:28,540
Well,

471
00:25:29,740 --> 00:25:31,400
what else did you dream about?

472
00:25:37,050 --> 00:25:38,080
If you suddenly want me to think about it,

473
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:39,250
I can't remember.

474
00:25:45,820 --> 00:25:49,150
Maybe this is the consequence
of wishing on a shooting star.

475
00:25:51,090 --> 00:25:52,930
Everyone's going to forget me.

476
00:25:54,130 --> 00:25:56,330
Forget everything about He Xiangyong.

477
00:25:57,930 --> 00:25:58,790
Shooting star?

478
00:25:59,230 --> 00:26:00,060
Make a wish?

479
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:05,370
I know it's hard to believe,

480
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:08,120
but it did happen to me.

481
00:26:11,430 --> 00:26:13,170
I told you that, too.

482
00:26:39,170 --> 00:26:40,230
Do you mind?

483
00:26:55,170 --> 00:26:56,770
I kind of believe it now.

484
00:27:36,590 --> 00:27:37,190
Do you want some?

485
00:27:37,190 --> 00:27:37,850
No.

486
00:27:46,390 --> 00:27:47,390
No.

487
00:27:48,910 --> 00:27:50,150
I didn't ask you.

488
00:28:00,890 --> 00:28:02,460
So noisy.

489
00:28:02,890 --> 00:28:05,550
It's so late. Your mom's gonna
yell at you again.

490
00:28:08,840 --> 00:28:10,900
You really can't remember anything?

491
00:28:11,500 --> 00:28:12,500
What?

492
00:28:13,170 --> 00:28:14,400
The two dishes.

493
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:16,060
Chicken feet and stinky tofu.

494
00:28:22,570 --> 00:28:24,770
You used to cling to me

495
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:25,940
all day long,

496
00:28:26,480 --> 00:28:27,450
but now...

497
00:28:28,490 --> 00:28:30,550
I don't know how to explain it anyway.

498
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:35,550
Stop playing.

499
00:28:36,490 --> 00:28:37,240
Go back.

500
00:28:37,580 --> 00:28:39,030
I'm almost done with this level.

501
00:28:39,030 --> 00:28:40,430
Whatever.

502
00:28:41,530 --> 00:28:42,630
Okay.

503
00:28:42,970 --> 00:28:45,300
Then don't text me later just
to yell at me.

504
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:48,290
Bye.

505
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:51,740
You really don't want to stay?

506
00:28:53,210 --> 00:28:54,810
Do you really want me to stay?

507
00:28:56,070 --> 00:28:56,990
Get lost.

508
00:28:59,100 --> 00:29:00,000
Bye.

509
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:27,000
Gosh. He really left.

510
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:35,100
Will those

511
00:30:35,950 --> 00:30:37,310
déjà vu memories

512
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:39,550
ever

513
00:30:40,750 --> 00:30:42,450
come back?

514
00:30:44,190 --> 00:30:45,490
Or...

515
00:30:46,550 --> 00:30:49,350
have I really been erased
from everyone's memory?

516
00:30:53,080 --> 00:31:00,430
[Epilogue]

517
00:31:04,630 --> 00:31:08,580
[For you]

518
00:31:38,470 --> 00:31:39,310
Hong?

519
00:31:40,510 --> 00:31:41,570
What are you doing?

520
00:31:43,060 --> 00:31:44,120
I'm

521
00:31:45,430 --> 00:31:46,690
watching shooting stars.

522
00:31:46,690 --> 00:31:48,150
Watching shooting stars?

523
00:31:48,960 --> 00:31:51,220
But it's daytime now.

524
00:31:51,630 --> 00:31:53,230
I know there are shooting stars
in the daytime.

525
00:31:53,230 --> 00:31:54,070
But...

526
00:31:54,290 --> 00:31:55,750
I don't think we can see it.

527
00:31:56,890 --> 00:31:57,880
Idiot.

528
00:31:58,080 --> 00:32:00,260
That's because you didn't look carefully.

529
00:32:00,260 --> 00:32:01,840
Look carefully.

530
00:32:01,860 --> 00:32:03,130
Look carefully?

531
00:32:04,630 --> 00:32:05,800
What do you mean?

532
00:32:06,140 --> 00:32:08,540
Do you want to wish upon
the shooting stars?

533
00:32:09,110 --> 00:32:10,210
Please.

534
00:32:10,380 --> 00:32:12,820
I've heard that story since I was a kid.

535
00:32:13,300 --> 00:32:15,500
Has anyone's wish ever truly come true?

536
00:32:16,550 --> 00:32:18,510
You've all been doing it wrong.

537
00:32:18,780 --> 00:32:19,920
Wrong way?

538
00:32:20,420 --> 00:32:21,180
What?

539
00:32:21,780 --> 00:32:22,750
Listen carefully.

540
00:32:22,750 --> 00:32:23,720
I'll only say it once.

541
00:32:23,720 --> 00:32:24,820
Okay.

542
00:32:26,710 --> 00:32:28,850
This is a shooting star fragment.

543
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:30,420
A shooting star fragment.

544
00:32:30,510 --> 00:32:31,980
You have to

545
00:32:32,010 --> 00:32:34,610
throw this shooting star fragment
into the sea

546
00:32:34,900 --> 00:32:36,100
when it comes .

547
00:32:38,670 --> 00:32:40,600
When the energy and your wish

548
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:41,940
combine,

549
00:32:42,670 --> 00:32:44,070
your wish will come true.

550
00:32:44,540 --> 00:32:46,210
Really?

551
00:32:47,780 --> 00:32:49,010
Do you want to try?

552
00:32:49,010 --> 00:32:50,680
Next time.

553
00:32:50,980 --> 00:32:53,440
I have to go back to help
with the guesthouse.

554
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:54,740
The tide is rising.

555
00:32:55,050 --> 00:32:56,650
Do you want to go back with me?

556
00:32:57,350 --> 00:32:58,120
Leave me alone.

557
00:32:58,120 --> 00:32:59,120
Go back now.

558
00:32:59,120 --> 00:32:59,960
Go.

559
00:32:59,960 --> 00:33:00,560
Okay.

560
00:33:00,560 --> 00:33:01,320
Be careful.

561
00:33:01,320 --> 00:33:02,360
Okay, I got it.

562
00:33:02,360 --> 00:33:02,850
Bye-bye.

563
00:33:02,850 --> 00:33:03,750
Okay, bye-bye.

564
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,380
Are you going to check in?

565
00:33:53,530 --> 00:33:59,810
[Next Episode]

566
00:33:54,440 --> 00:33:55,610
Chen Haowei.

567
00:33:55,610 --> 00:33:56,410
Sir.

568
00:33:56,410 --> 00:33:57,610
Are you checking in?

569
00:33:58,350 --> 00:34:00,020
I like you!

570
00:34:00,020 --> 00:34:01,690
I like you!

571
00:34:03,930 --> 00:34:05,760
Have you heard of the cell memory

572
00:34:05,780 --> 00:34:07,230
or body memory?

573
00:34:07,250 --> 00:34:08,480
Your mind may forget,

574
00:34:08,989 --> 00:34:10,760
